Defendant Glen S Tessman in court, in custody, with attorney Daniel P Fay.   Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed Sentence of:

6 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 270 days)
- 3 Years of Initial Confinement
- 3 Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Be involved in a 12 step program within 30 days and within 60 days obtain a sponsor/mentor;
- Perform 20 hours of community service in a drug/alcohol rehabilitation service each year with the last 20 hours to be completed within the last 90 days of supervision.
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge;

DL REVOCATION:  36 Months
IID: 36 Months

Fine : $5833 
DNA surcharge: $250.00
Blood Draw Fee:  $35.00 to be paid to Waukesha County Clerk of Courts to be forwarded to   Waukesha Police Department.
(To be paid at the rate of $150.00  per month commencing the 4th month of extended supervision)

VICTIM IMPACT PANEL:  Within first 6 months of release onto extended supervision

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
